Okechukwu Nnodim, Abuja The Federal Government is working to diversify the Niger Delta region through the implementation of emergency agricultural projects in the oil rich area, the Minister of State for Budget and National Planning, Clem Agba, said on Monday. Agba said this in Abuja at a stakeholders’ meeting on the proposed ‘Emergency Agricultural Projects in Diversification of Niger Delta and the Nation’s Non-Oil Economy.’ He said the agricultural projects that target the Niger Delta region and the nation’s non-oil economy would have a range of benefits. Copyright PUNCH.
